            <scopecontent id="aspace_f9dca2e213c6054d4aafadcde28eb1ae">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Lowenthal's speeches and publications comprise the largest part of the collection. The speeches are directed at a variety of audiences, ranging from faculty and students to the Commencement speech of 1948 Lowenthal delivered in place of President Herbert Davis. Almost all the speeches are typewritten. Publications include her dissertation while at Columbia <title render="italic">The Ricardian Socialists</title> and her pamphlet <title render="italic">Labor Policy of Oneida Community Ltd.</title>"</p>
